pan><span>Feel free to pause the video as needed.</span></span></p><h2><spa=
n><u><strong><span>Lab tasks:</span></strong></u></span></h2><h2><span><spa=
n>Step 1: Define your app&nbsp;</span></span></h2><p data-text-variant=3D"b=
ody1"><span><span>Once in AI Studio, make sure you are signed in with your =
Google account. Next, navigate to =E2=80=9CBuild AI apps=E2=80=9D. In the p=
rompt box on the Build page, describe the Tiebreaker app:&nbsp;</span></spa=
n></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><var><span>I want an app called =
The Tiebreaker that helps me make decisions. I want to provide a decision t=
hat I need to make, and I'd love AI's help in showing me different pros and=
 cons. This can be through a pros and cons list, a comparison table, or eve=
n a SWOT analysis.</span></var></span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><s=
pan><span>When you are ready, click the =E2=80=9CBuild=E2=80=9D button.</sp=
an></span></p><h2><span><span>Step 2: Test your application&nbsp;</span></s=
pan></h2><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Once the app interface =
appears, put it to the test with a real-world scenario.</span></span></p><p=
 data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Locate the input field (e.g. "What=
 decision do you need to make?"), and enter:&nbsp;</span></span></p><p data=
-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><var><span>Should I offer my software for fre=
e with paid features, or charge a flat $20/month premium plan?</span></var>=
</span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Then, select an analy=
sis type (e.g., Pros and Cons List).</span></span></p><p data-text-variant=
=3D"body1"><span><span>Click =E2=80=9CGet</span></span><span><strong><span>=
 </span></strong></span><span><span>Analysis=E2=80=9D and review the result=
s generated.&nbsp;</span></span></p><h2><span><span>Step 3: Troubleshoot an=
d "Auto-fix" errors&nbsp;</span></span></h2><p data-text-variant=3D"body1">=
<span><span>If the app breaks, or stops working, don=E2=80=99t start over. =
This is part of the process.&nbsp;</span></span></p><p data-text-variant=3D=
"body1"><span><span>When an error occurs, you=E2=80=99ll see the error and =
a button for =E2=80=9CAuto-fix=E2=80=9D appear in the prompt box on the lef=
t.&nbsp;</span></span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Click =
=E2=80=9CAuto fix=E2=80=9D and the model will analyze the error, think thro=
ugh the solution, and rewrite the code to fix the bug.</span></span></p><h2=
><span><span>Step 4: Verify the fix</span></span><span><strong><span>&nbsp;=
</span></strong></span></h2><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Afte=
r the =E2=80=9CAuto-fix=E2=80=9D is complete, test the app again to ensure =
all features are working.</span></span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><=
span><span>Enter a new decision:&nbsp;</span></span></p><p data-text-varian=
t=3D"body1"><span><var><span>What should I eat tonight: Sushi or Chinese fo=
od?</span></var></span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Then,=
 select =E2=80=9CComparison Table.=E2=80=9D</span></span></p><p data-text-v=
ariant=3D"body1"><span><span>Click =E2=80=9CGet Analysis=E2=80=9D and ensur=
e the results display correctly in the new format.</span></span></p><h2><sp=
an><u><strong><span>Next steps:</span></strong></u></span></h2><p data-text=
-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>Reflect on what you=E2=80=99ve just created =
and consider other decision-making frameworks you use at work.&nbsp;</span>=
</span></p><p data-text-variant=3D"body1"><span><span>When you are satisfie=
